The tale is full of improbabilities. rem: = rem firmiliarem as in 1. — patribus bonis interdici solet: ‘fathers are often pre· vented from managing their property ’. The fragment of the xn tables here re· ferred to is thus given in Dirksen's edition: sei fouriosos aut prodicos (prodigus) escit (erit) adcnatorum centiliomque (gentiliumque) eius pote- stas estod, i. e. the agnates (male relatives whose kinship with the furio- sus is derived through males) and members of his gens are to administer his property.
